HEADWORD: Reverberative
<hw>Re*ver"ber*a*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of the
nature of reverberation; tending to reverberate; reflective.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This <qex>reverberative</qex> influence is that which we have
intended above, as the influence of the mass upon its centers.</q>
<rj><qau>I. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reverberator</ent>⟦br⟧
